Class CompartmentGlyph

    Serializable, Cloneable, TreeNode, NamedSBase, SBase, UniqueNamedSBase, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    public class CompartmentGlyph
extends AbstractReferenceGlyph
    The CompartmentGlyph class is derived from GraphicalObject and inherits its attributes. Additionally it has tow optional attributes: compartment and order.

      • setCompartment

        public void setCompartment(Compartment compartment)
        The compartment attribute is used to add a reference to the id of the corresponding Compartment in the Model. Since the compartment is optional, the user can specify Compartments in the Layout that are not part of the Model. This attribute is optional.
        Parameters:
        compartment -

      • setOrder

        public void setOrder(double order)
        The order attribute is an optional attribute of type Double. It is there to handle the case where compartments in a layout overlap, and tools want to clearly disambiguate which CompartmentGlyph is on top of the other. The order attribute follows the coordinate system. There are z dimension points into a screen; thus, an element with a lower order value will be in front of an elements with a higher value. If not specified, the order is undefined and tools are free to display the compartment glyphs in the order that best fits their needs. Note: if z coordinates are used (and this order is seemingly redundant), the order can still be used to disambiguate drawing order.
        Parameters:
        order -
